<strong>Turkey – New Regulations for Labelling and Marking on Fibre Composition in Textile Products</strong>

On April 25, 2015, Turkey’s Ministry of Customs and Trade published Regulation No. 29337 on <b><u>Textile fibre names and the labelling of the fibre composition of textile products and marking</u></b>. The regulation came in force on April 25, 2015, except for Article 13 "textile products comprising non-textile parts of animal origin", which will become effective on January 1, 2016. This regulation is in compliance with the European Union Legislation 1007/2011.  

The following products are considered textile products to fall within the scope in the Regulation:
<ul>
	<li>Products containing at least 80% by weight of textile fibres;</li>
	<li>Furniture that consists of at least 80% by weight of textile components, umbrellas and awnings;</li>
	<li>The textile components of the following products (provided that they consist of at least 80% by weight of textile components):
<ol>
	<li>The upper layer of multi-layer floor coverings</li>
	<li>Bed covers</li>
	<li>Covers for camping products</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
Composition shall be specified if textiles are combined with other products or form part of a combination.

Labelling or marking should be done in Turkish with required information in accordance with the Regulations by means of a label attached to the product in form of sewing, embroidery or any other means of technology to specify the required information directly on the textile products.

