<strong>Update - Japan Azo Restriction in Textile Products</strong>

In July 2015, The Japan Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare (MHLW) announced the Ministerial Ordinance (No. 124) to designate azo compounds as hazardous substances and restrict the presence of the specified 24 aromatic amines with a limit of less than 30 mg/kg by GC-MS analysis.

The household products that fall within this scope include: 
<ul>
	<li>Textile products with azo dyes – covers, underwear, sleepwear, socks caps, bedding, towels, bath mats and related products</li>
	<li>Leather and/or fur products with azo dyes – garments, caps, hats and related products</li>
</ul>

The 24 specified aromatic amines were listed in <a href="http://www.ansecogroup.com/regrecap/5871/" target="_blank">Regulatory Recap: Issue 2, May 2015</a>.

